---
import Layout from "~/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Account — Stagea"
  description="Single sign-on across every Stagea service. Not yet available."
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Account</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-(--color-muted)">
      Single sign-on across forum, wiki, blog, and shop. Will exchange an OIDC
      session from Keycloak (planned <code>auth/</code> service) for a signed
      header that downstream services trust.
    </p>

    <div
      class="mt-10 rounded-xl border border-dashed border-(--color-border) bg-(--color-surface)/30 p-10 text-center text-sm text-(--color-muted)"
    >
      Not implemented yet. The route exists so the navbar's "Sign in" link
      resolves; the login flow lands when <code>auth/</code> is scaffolded.
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
